        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 1:48PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near North Carolina Zoo. These storms were nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
High Point, Asheboro, Randleman, North Carolina Zoo, Siler City,
Goldston, Seagrove, Archdale, Trinity, and Pleasant Garden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Very heavy rain can be expected due to the slow movement of this
storm. Prolonged heavy rain will result in ponding of water on
roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and minor flooding of
creeks and streams. Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra
caution to avoid hydroplaning.</instruction>
